                    <tr>
                      <td width="41%"><font size="3">Torres Strait Islands</font></td>
                      <td width="59%" align="right"> <font size="3"><img src="../../img/flags/flg_aust.gif" width="70" height="35"></font></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" height="1">
                    <tr background="../../img/maps/cp_tile.gif" valign="top"> 
                      <td background="../../img/maps/cp_tile.gif"><img src="../../img/maps/cp_space.gif" width="37" height="1"></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  <p class="profile_intro">The Torres Strait Islands are part 
                    of the Australian state of Queensland. Situated between mainland 
                    Australia and Papua New Guinea, the Torres Strait Islands 
                    are the only part of Australia sharing a border with another 
                    country. 
                  <p align="center"><img src="../../img/maps/cp_torres.gif" width="463" height="349" alt="Map of Torres Strait Islands"></p>
                  <br>
                  <h5><a name="facts"></a>Facts and Figures</h5>
